Oktoberfest was more than a beer festival to Felix; it was a part of his heritage.
It was the first he’d seen of the blighted flowers, and he still held a spark of hope that many had lost. He ransacked Vigo’s workshop in hopes of discovering a miracle.
At 18, Felix visited the Swiss Alps with his mother, an attempt to reconnect years after losing his father. Nothing felt the same.
Felix explored the city to admire the striking contemporary architecture that makes Seoul so unique.
He attended a classy event in the hopes of finding an investor for his ambitious architectural project that lacked funding.
During the holiday break, Felix crammed a last-minute project in his work, designing the new annexe for an art museum in Barcelona.
